HEADWORD: Quinch
<hw>Quinch</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Cf. OD.
<ets>quincken</ets> to quiver, shake, Fries. <ets>quink</ets> hovering.
Cf. <er>Quich</er>.]</ety> <def>To stir; to wince.</def>
